### 2. Recording an Observation (Conventional + Native Histogram)

**File:** `prom_histogram.go`, lines 766-768 and 900-912

```go
func (h *histogram) Observe(v float64) {
    h.observe(v, h.findBucket(v))
}

// observe is the implementation for Observe without the findBucket part.
func (h *histogram) observe(v float64, bucket int) {
    doSparse := h.nativeHistogramSchema > math.MinInt32 && !math.IsNaN(v)
    n := atomic.AddUint64(&h.countAndHotIdx, 1)
    hotCounts := h.counts[n>>63]
    hotCounts.observe(v, bucket, doSparse)
    if doSparse {
        h.limitBuckets(hotCounts, v, bucket)
    }
}
```

`observe` uses a lock-free hot/cold counting scheme: the most-significant bit of `countAndHotIdx` selects which of the two `histogramCounts` is "hot" (receiving new writes). The remaining 63 bits count in-flight observations.

